.TH "regmap_field_update_bits_base" 9 "regmap_field_update_bits_base" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
regmap_field_update_bits_base \- Perform a read/modify/write cycle a register field.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" regmap_field_update_bits_base
.BI "(struct regmap_field *field "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int val "  ","
.BI "bool *change "  ","
.BI "bool async "  ","
.BI "bool force "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "field" 12
Register field to write to
.IP "mask" 12
Bitmask to change
.IP "val" 12
Value to be written
.IP "change" 12
Boolean indicating if a write was done
.IP "async" 12
Boolean indicating asynchronously
.IP "force" 12
Boolean indicating use force update
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perform a read/modify/write cycle on the register field with change,
async, force option.

A value of zero will be returned on success, a negative errno will
be returned in error cases.
